subSubSection.paragraph:
Compared to the original description (
Hale 1972
), the investigated type material showed some differences in the thallus anatomy. The thicknesses mentioned by Hale for the upper cortex (14.0−18.0 
µm
), the algal layer (10.0−15.0 
µm
), medulla (70.0−90.0 
µm
) and lower cortex (12 
µm
) are smaller than those found here, especially for the medulla. The ascospores found were slightly larger.
